    <!-- Facts -->
    <string name="fact_1">Your heart is 73% water — staying hydrated helps maintain healthy blood pressure.</string>
    <string name="fact_2">The water you drink contains atoms that passed through dinosaurs — Earth\'s water is 4.5 billion years old!</string>
    <string name="fact_3">Even mild dehydration (1–3%) can impair your mood and concentration.</string>
    <string name="fact_4">Hot water can freeze faster than cold — called the Mpemba Effect!</string>
    <string name="fact_5">Drinking water boosts metabolism by 24–30% for 1–1.5 hours.</string>
    <string name="fact_6">A black hole 12 billion light-years away holds 140 trillion times more water than all of Earth\'s oceans!</string>
    <string name="fact_7" formatted="false">The human body is about 60% water for men, 55% for women.</string>
    <string name="fact_8">Water is the only natural substance found as liquid, gas, and solid on Earth!</string>
    <string name="fact_9">Proper hydration reduces the risk of kidney stones by up to 50%.</string>
    <string name="fact_10">Your brain has no water reserves — even 2% dehydration can temporarily shrink brain tissue!</string>
    <string name="fact_11">Your nerves and heart both use electricity — water helps conduct the signals!</string>
    <string name="fact_12" formatted="false">97% of Earth\'s water is salty, 2% is locked in ice — only 1% is accessible freshwater.</string>
